∞
exp(2πiντ ) × Mˆ (0)Mˆ (τ ) qm dτ
−∞

(60)

with β being 1/(kbT ), V being the sample’s volume, c being the speed of light, n(ν) being the index of refraction, ǫ0 being the vacuum permittivity, and Mˆ being the quantum mechanical total dipole moment operator. Iftimie and Tuckerman applied
the harmonic approximation expressed in

∞

