Applying this expression with the four-term Blackman windowed Fourier transform approach led to sufﬁcient accuracy based on a relatively short trajectory (10 ps), i.e. the authors found excellent agreement between the experimentally obtained spectra for liquid and solid water. Using this approach and decomposing the total dipole moment

